grub-gfxboot (0.97-41) unstable; urgency=low

  * fetch ext4_fix_variable_sized_inodes by Colin Watson <cjwatson@ubuntu.com>
    from Ubuntu: Add support for ext4 variable sized inodes (LP: #345488). 
    This is backwardly compatible with ext2 ext3 fixed sized inodes.

 -- Stefan Lippers-Hollmann <s.l-h@gmx.de>  Sun, 24 May 2009 18:53:42 +0200

grub-gfxboot (0.97-40) unstable; urgency=low

  * switch from dh_clean -k to dh_prep, to become compliant with debhelper 7
    and to make lintian happy.

 -- Stefan Lippers-Hollmann <s.l-h@gmx.de>  Tue, 27 Jan 2009 17:22:19 +0100

grub-gfxboot (0.97-39) unstable; urgency=low

  * sync with Debian svn r1153:
    [ Robert Millan ]
    - patches/xfs_freeze.diff: Replace with a new patch, which thaws XFS 
      immediately after freezing it.  (Closes: #239111, #243835, #246111, 
      #309218, #425367) hopefully for good this time.  Thanks everyone who 
      sent their feedback, too many to list them here.
  * refresh series.

