grub-gfxboot (0.97-36) unstable; urgency=low

  * make lintian happy and depend on ${misc:Depends}.
  * sync with Debian svn r1124:
    [ Robert Millan ]
    - update-grub: Do not attempt to detect CONFIG_PARAVIRT Xen images.
      Thanks Raphaël Hertzog et al.  (Closes: #500336)

 -- Stefan Lippers-Hollmann <s.l-h@gmx.de>  Mon, 08 Dec 2008 22:36:53 +0100

grub-gfxboot (0.97-35) unstable; urgency=low

  * drop the conflict with lilo, while this conflict and the arguments taken 
    below are essentially still true, currently does more harm (by dereffering
    installing grub/ removing lilo) than good (the device.map changes are 
    needed for quite some users upgrading from pre-libata setups for the first
    time since update-grub relies on grub-common).

 -- Stefan Lippers-Hollmann <s.l-h@gmx.de>  Tue, 04 Nov 2008 01:44:44 +0100

grub-gfxboot (0.97-34) unstable; urgency=low

  * conflict with lilo until the next regular maintainer upload, this is a 
    pity, but required due to the following reasons:
    - unconfigured lilo installations are dangerous on upgrades, #504376.
    - it is broken in combination with a default initramfs-tools setup, 
      #479607.
    - grub does not allow bootloader coexistance on the system.
    - lilo is unlikely to be part of squeeze, cf.
      http://lists.debian.org/debian-devel/2008/06/msg00400.html
  * sync with Debian svn r1109:
    [ Robert Millan ]
    - update-grub: Try to regenerate device.map when grub-probe fails (and
      inform the user about it).  Thanks Raphaël Hertzog.  (Closes: #501306).

 -- Stefan Lippers-Hollmann <s.l-h@gmx.de>  Tue, 04 Nov 2008 01:03:36 +0100

grub-gfxboot (0.97-33) unstable; urgency=low

  * fix bug files.

 -- Stefan Lippers-Hollmann <s.l-h@gmx.de>  Sun, 14 Sep 2008 00:03:03 +0200

grub-gfxboot (0.97-32) unstable; urgency=low

  * sync with Debian svn r1067 (0.97-51).
  * add changes from 0.97-47:
    [ Robert Millan ]
    - update-grub: Send grub-probe stderr output to /dev/null.
      (Closes: #495909)
  * add changes from 0.97-46:
    [ Robert Millan ]
    - Bring the rc/pre/etc exceptions back again when comparing versions.
      (Closes: #493389)
  * add changes from 0.97-45:
    [ Felix Zielcke ]
    - use dpkg --compare-versions in update-grub.  (Closes: #493389)
  * add changes from 0.97-44:
    [ Robert Millan ]
    - Ignore -y option.  When menu.lst doesn't exist, it's always generated.
      (Closes: #492213)
    - NEWS: Add note recommending that users update their GRUB installs.
      (Closes: #451701)
  * add changes from 0.97-43:
    [ Felix Zielcke ]
    - debian/rules: changed cvs rules to svn
    - Update Standards version to 3.8.0. No changes need.
    - add 2 overrides to make lintian happy
    [ Robert Millan ]
    - Fix regression in patches/ext3_256byte_inode.diff, thanks Eric Sandeen
      <sandeen@redhat.com>.  (Closes: #491076)
  * add changes from 0.97-42:
    [ Robert Millan ]
    - Avoid passing UUIDs to Linux when "/dev/disk/by-uuid/${root_uuid}" does
      not exist
    - control (grub): Add a note in description pointing at GRUB 2.
      (Closes: #488304)
    - patches/use_grub-probe_in_grub-install.diff: Use grub-mkdevicemap when
      device.map needs to be regenerated (this brings in Virtio support, and
      probably others).
      (Closes: #491745)
  * integrate recent Debian changes in grub-gfxboot.

 -- Stefan Lippers-Hollmann <s.l-h@gmx.de>  Sat, 13 Sep 2008 23:49:59 +0200

grub-gfxboot (0.97-31) unstable; urgency=low

  * add patch to distinguish between old-style ext2 format and dynamic
    revision ext2 formats, provided by Eric Sandeen <sandeen@redhat.com>.
  * refresh series.

 -- Stefan Lippers-Hollmann <s.l-h@gmx.de>  Tue, 22 Jul 2008 17:55:48 +0200

grub-gfxboot (0.97-30) unstable; urgency=low

  * fix bashisms in debian/grub-reboot instead of harcoding bash.
  * add changes from 0.97-41:
    [ Robert Millan ]
    - Fix problem with root= argument generation in loop-AES.  Reported by
      Max Vozeler.  (Closes: #488016)
    - update-grub: Only special-case Xen detection for older Linux images
      without CONFIG_PARAVIRT.  Thanks Ian Campbell.  (Closes: #468824)
  * add changes from 0.97-40:
    [ Robert Millan ]
    - Remove obsolete note about initrd size.  (Closes: #482611)
    - update-grub: Use filesystem UUIDs when available.
  * add changes from 0.97-39:
    [ Robert Millan ]
    - New upstream snapshot.
      + Fixes license violation.  (Closes: #479623)
      + patches/1tib_disk_limit.diff: Merged.
      + patches/geometry-26kernel.diff: Resync.
    - Adjust make_system_path_relative_to_its_root() not to print trailing
      slashes.  (Closes: #479169)
    - Handle relative paths for splash images.  Thanks Petter
      Reinholdtsen.  (Closes: #477791)
    - Support for Xen style xvd[a-z] devices.  Thanks Ian Campbell.
      (Closes: #456776)
    - Document that grub-set-default counts entries starting with 0.
      (Closes: #451709)
  * add changes from 0.97-38:
    [ Robert Millan ]
    - patches/use_grub-probe_in_grub-install.diff: Reinstate RAID1 hack.
      Based on patch from Goswin Brederlow <goswin-v-b@web.de>.
      (Closes: #478547, #464146)
  * add changes from 0.97-37:
    [ Robert Millan ]
    - update-grub: Fix detection of /dev/md/X RAID.  Thanks Stephen Kitt.
      (Closes: #477998)
    - update-grub/grub-install: Pass --device-map to grub-probe.  Thanks
      segmentation@ntlworld.com.  (Closes: #476833)
    - script: Fix use of uninitialised $i.
    - update-grub: Make relative path resolution more robust.  (Closes: #478006)
  * add changes from 0.97-36:
    [ Robert Millan ]
    - Add debian/script.
    - Set grub-reboot interpreter to /bin/bash.  (Closes: #473685)
    - update-grub: Create device.map if it doesn't exist.  (Closes: #473889)
  * add changes from 0.97-35:
    [ Robert Millan ]
    - Upload to unstable.
  * add changes from 0.97-34:
    [ Robert Millan ]
    - patches/128gib_disk_limit.diff: Extend disk addressing up to 2 TiB.
      (Closes: #450951)
  * add changes from 0.97-33, again:
    [ Robert Millan ]
    - control (grub): Suggest multiboot-doc.
    - update-grub: Rewrite find_device() and convert() using grub-probe from
      grub-common package. (Closes: #435708, #443897, #463274, #301373, #284790)
    - patches/use_grub-probe_in_grub-install.diff: Do the same for grub-install.
      (Closes: #441080)
  * refresh and fix patches.
  * fix syntax error in update-grub.8.
  * compile with gcc-4.3.

 -- Stefan Lippers-Hollmann <s.l-h@gmx.de>  Sun, 06 Jul 2008 01:13:59 +0200

grub-gfxboot (0.97-29) unstable; urgency=low

  * drop use_grub-probe_in_grub-install.diff and revert modifications for 
    update-grub from 0.97-33, the changes to grub-install don't work with 
    --root-directory yet.
  * drop dependency on grub-common.

 -- Stefan Lippers-Hollmann <s.l-h@gmx.de>  Tue, 11 Mar 2008 22:03:44 +0100

grub-gfxboot (0.97-28) unstable; urgency=low

  * add changes from 0.97-33, we don't import 0.97-32:
    [ Robert Millan ]
    - update-grub: Rewrite find_device() and convert() using grub-probe from
      grub-common package.  (Closes: #435708, #443897, #463274, #301373,
      #284790)
    - patches/use_grub-probe_in_grub-install.diff: Do the same for
      grub-install. Closes: #441080)
  * drop SuSE's grub-install-fix-UUID_LABEL.diff, its functionality is now
    provided by Debian's use_grub-probe_in_grub-install.diff.
  * drop grub-gfxboot-doc, "grub-doc" has been renamed to multiboot-doc and
    does the job just as well.
  * refer to multiboot-doc wherever needed.
  * restore accidentally removed grub-gfxboot.docs.

 -- Stefan Lippers-Hollmann <s.l-h@gmx.de>  Tue, 11 Mar 2008 21:25:25 +0100

